WEBVTT

1
00:00:22.063 --> 00:00:24.691
♪ There's neon lights in New York City ♪

2
00:00:24.774 --> 00:00:26.985
♪ Bumper stickers that read
"I voted for Willie" ♪

3
00:00:27.068 --> 00:00:28.319
♪ Ain't it evident? ♪

4
00:00:28.903 --> 00:00:31.114
♪ It's a small world we're living in ♪

5
00:00:32.615 --> 00:00:37.245
♪ Skyscrapers may kiss the sky ♪

6
00:00:37.912 --> 00:00:41.166
♪ But everywhere's got a countryside ♪

7
00:00:45.503 --> 00:00:48.506
Guess we're not in New York
anymore. are we. Biscuit?

8
00:01:05.023 --> 00:01:07.609
♪ We're all stars in a different show ♪

9
00:01:07.692 --> 00:01:10.236
♪ Singing along with the radio ♪

10
00:01:10.320 --> 00:01:13.239
♪ All the same different shades of grey ♪

11
00:01:13.323 --> 00:01:16.159
♪ Just trying to enjoy the ride ♪

12
00:01:16.242 --> 00:01:20.246
-♪ Everywhere's got a countryside ♪
-Morning.

13
00:01:21.581 --> 00:01:25.835
How you doing. honey? You good? You good?

14
00:01:25.919 --> 00:01:30.173
♪ Countryside ♪

15
00:01:36.888 --> 00:01:38.264
Where's he at now?

16
00:01:38.348 --> 00:01:40.350
Giving old Tino a piece of his mind

17
00:01:40.433 --> 00:01:42.519
about the controlled burn
at the fence line.

18
00:01:43.812 --> 00:01:45.730
Boys aren't happy.
Rough few months.

19
00:01:45.814 --> 00:01:49.275
I know. Don't worry. boys. We're gonna
get rid of him soon enough. All right?

20
00:01:50.527 --> 00:01:51.528
And if we don't?

21
00:01:51.611 --> 00:01:55.240
If we don't. you're gonna have to put me
out of my misery like an old barn dog.

22
00:01:59.577 --> 00:02:03.039
Ah. clue me in. boys. What's so funny?

23
00:02:03.832 --> 00:02:04.916
Huh?

24
00:02:07.001 --> 00:02:11.005
Where do I start? Fact that you got
your butt whooped in the last election.

25
00:02:11.089 --> 00:02:14.884
or that when it comes to ranching. you
don't know your elbow from your asshole?

26
00:02:17.220 --> 00:02:18.096
Careful. son.

27
00:02:18.179 --> 00:02:19.180
Or what?

28
00:02:20.306 --> 00:02:23.935
Are you gonna steal control of this ranch
out from under me? Wait. you already did.

29
00:02:24.018 --> 00:02:25.186
That I did.

30
00:02:27.897 --> 00:02:31.151
But everyone in this room
should take note of that fact.

31
00:02:31.818 --> 00:02:34.529
There's another Kirkland
in charge now.

32
00:02:35.864 --> 00:02:37.490
And if you don't like it.

33
00:02:38.032 --> 00:02:41.202
don't let the barn door hit you
in the ass on the way out.

34
00:02:41.286 --> 00:02:42.579
That includes you.

35
00:02:45.331 --> 00:02:47.876
You done playing big man.
or can we get back to work?

36
00:02:49.085 --> 00:02:50.545
Hey!

37
00:02:59.721 --> 00:03:00.763
Don't test me.

38
00:03:09.522 --> 00:03:12.483
-Matty. rotate that herd.
-Yes. sir.

39
00:03:12.567 --> 00:03:14.527
Sterlin. make sure we re-up that alfalfa.

40
00:03:14.611 --> 00:03:15.862
-Good work.
-Uh-huh.

41
00:03:20.742 --> 00:03:21.826
What's eating you?

42
00:03:21.910 --> 00:03:25.872
Seen the strangest thing this morning.
A little silver Audi parked by the pond.

43
00:03:25.955 --> 00:03:26.956
Oh.

44
00:03:27.040 --> 00:03:30.251
See a woman on her cell phone.
can't find her way off the ranch.

45
00:03:30.335 --> 00:03:32.670
I had to race out of there. all right?

46
00:03:33.171 --> 00:03:35.381
Yancy needed help with a baby calf.

47
00:03:38.426 --> 00:03:39.636
Did you show her out?

48
00:03:39.719 --> 00:03:40.845
I did.

49
00:03:41.721 --> 00:03:42.639
Thank you.

50
00:03:44.390 --> 00:03:46.142
-What?
-I'm not judging your

51
00:03:47.101 --> 00:03:49.187
revolving door of lady friends.

52
00:03:49.270 --> 00:03:52.398
Wait. It kind of feels like you are. Jake.

53
00:03:52.482 --> 00:03:54.442
Figured you might think
to rein it in a bit.

54
00:03:54.525 --> 00:03:56.027
Now. why would I do that?

55
00:03:57.111 --> 00:04:00.031
Because… she's back.

56
00:04:32.355 --> 00:04:33.898
Welcome home. sis!

57
00:04:36.359 --> 00:04:37.443
Get over here.

58
00:04:42.699 --> 00:04:43.825
Six months.

59
00:04:43.908 --> 00:04:44.993
Six months.

60
00:04:45.076 --> 00:04:46.494
Ah. I missed you.

61
00:04:47.412 --> 00:04:48.579
I missed you. too.

62
00:04:48.663 --> 00:04:51.291
-Look. hear me out.
-Mm-hm.

63
00:04:51.374 --> 00:04:54.127
You have to promise not to get mad. okay?

64
00:04:54.210 --> 00:04:56.629
She wouldn't take no for an answer.

65
00:04:56.713 --> 00:04:57.922
How's my girl?

66
00:05:03.303 --> 00:05:04.345
Hi. Mom.

67
00:05:05.471 --> 00:05:09.392
We were chit-chatting and your sister
let on about your big welcome home party.

68
00:05:09.475 --> 00:05:11.561
"Surprise." Mom.

69
00:05:12.145 --> 00:05:13.271
Surprise party.

70
00:05:13.354 --> 00:05:14.689
Mom.

71
00:05:15.565 --> 00:05:17.191
Not anymore.

72
00:05:17.275 --> 00:05:20.361
-I just had to be here for you.
-When was the last time you were here?

73
00:05:20.445 --> 00:05:22.363
Too long. That's exactly my point.

74
00:05:22.447 --> 00:05:24.907
-Well. there's more to it. right?
-Mm. definitely.

75
00:05:24.991 --> 00:05:27.660
-Why are you two pitching a fit?
-Because we know you.

76
00:05:27.744 --> 00:05:29.954
-Know what I should do while I'm here?
-Mm.

77
00:05:30.038 --> 00:05:31.998
Trying to talk you
into going back to New York.

78
00:05:32.081 --> 00:05:33.541
I… I'm serious.

79
00:05:33.624 --> 00:05:35.460
When I was visiting you there.

80
00:05:35.543 --> 00:05:38.171
seeing the life you were living.
should be living…

81
00:05:38.880 --> 00:05:41.716
Look. I'm not about
to give relationship advice.

82
00:05:41.799 --> 00:05:44.344
Thank you. I appreciate that.

83
00:05:44.427 --> 00:05:46.346
Speaking of. how is Roger?

84
00:05:46.429 --> 00:05:47.764
-William.
-William.

85
00:05:47.847 --> 00:05:48.890
Number five.

86
00:05:49.515 --> 00:05:51.517
William's fine. Everything's fine.

87
00:05:52.143 --> 00:05:53.394
Oh. you girls.

88
00:05:54.270 --> 00:05:57.190
Can I not spend quality time
with my two beautiful daughters?

89
00:05:57.273 --> 00:05:58.858
Is that not allowed?

90
00:05:58.941 --> 00:06:00.401
Yeah. it's allowed. Mom.

91
00:06:00.485 --> 00:06:02.528
Good. One of y'all put on some coffee.

92
00:06:02.612 --> 00:06:04.238
I'm gonna make Texas Rangers.

93
00:06:04.906 --> 00:06:07.075
I still got it.

94
00:06:07.158 --> 00:06:08.451
I'll get the coffee.

95
00:06:10.244 --> 00:06:11.579
Oh. I still got it.

96
00:06:11.662 --> 00:06:13.790
Mm. you still got it. Mom.

97
00:07:01.754 --> 00:07:02.839
I'll be back.

98
00:07:04.215 --> 00:07:05.883
Hey. How'd it go?

99
00:07:05.967 --> 00:07:08.052
-Hi. Good. Yeah.
-Yeah?

100
00:07:08.136 --> 00:07:09.846
-Great.
-Yeah? Hell. yeah.

101
00:07:09.929 --> 00:07:12.306
I knew our late night
tutoring sessions would pay off.

102
00:07:12.390 --> 00:07:14.100
-Yeah.
-Hell with cheer. huh?

103
00:07:14.183 --> 00:07:18.271
If your SATs are good enough. UT might
consider giving you another scholarship.

104
00:07:18.354 --> 00:07:20.815
Yeah. Yeah. who knows?

105
00:07:20.898 --> 00:07:21.899
Just take the W.

106
00:07:24.777 --> 00:07:25.987
Okay.

107
00:07:26.070 --> 00:07:30.491
Only… if we can get our tutoring sessions
back to their original purpose.

108
00:07:30.575 --> 00:07:31.659
Oh. yeah?

109
00:07:32.869 --> 00:07:33.953
Show me.

110
00:07:35.121 --> 00:07:36.122
Okay.

111
00:07:38.082 --> 00:07:40.042
Yeah. Yeah?

112
00:07:43.588 --> 00:07:45.256
Hey. Quinn. welcome back.

113
00:07:45.339 --> 00:07:46.340
Hey.

114
00:08:39.352 --> 00:08:40.978
You're back.

115
00:08:44.190 --> 00:08:45.316
I'm back.

116
00:08:46.025 --> 00:08:48.861
Look at you. Look at this place.

117
00:08:48.945 --> 00:08:50.363
I know. right?

118
00:08:50.446 --> 00:08:54.617
Yeah. so all those times you said busy.
you were just massively downplaying it?

119
00:08:54.700 --> 00:08:56.410
-Not too bad. huh?
-No.

120
00:08:56.494 --> 00:08:59.413
And… we're actually turning a profit.

121
00:09:01.916 --> 00:09:05.753
Some of the other businesses around here.
though. not so lucky.

122
00:09:06.254 --> 00:09:08.673
-Yeah. I heard Miss Ollie's closed.
-Yep.

123
00:09:08.756 --> 00:09:10.841
-And Maeve's.
-Mm-hm.

124
00:09:11.759 --> 00:09:15.137
I mean. you said it was bad.
but I didn't realize how bad.

125
00:09:15.221 --> 00:09:19.433
Yeah. well.
once the pipeline was in. AWP cut bait.

126
00:09:19.517 --> 00:09:21.852
All that money dried up.

127
00:09:21.936 --> 00:09:24.021
Half dozen ranches folded.

128
00:09:24.105 --> 00:09:27.149
-A bunch of them sold out and cashed in.
-Hm.

129
00:09:27.817 --> 00:09:29.151
Davis?

130
00:09:29.235 --> 00:09:30.319
Davis.

131
00:09:36.993 --> 00:09:40.705
You think that'll really work out.
him and Paula Jo reconciling?

132
00:09:43.749 --> 00:09:45.793
I mean. I guess with Reid at A&M now.

133
00:09:45.876 --> 00:09:49.547
he figured he'd just take the money
and head to Austin.

134
00:09:49.630 --> 00:09:52.550
Oh. I sure know how to pick 'em.

135
00:09:52.633 --> 00:09:54.677
Okay. enough about Davis.

136
00:09:55.469 --> 00:09:56.929
-How is NYC?
-Ah.

137
00:09:57.513 --> 00:09:58.639
If I'm honest…

138
00:09:59.473 --> 00:10:03.519
Playing in front of all those people.
it really filled the cup.

139
00:10:04.979 --> 00:10:07.690
But so did this.
And I was ready to be home.

140
00:10:07.773 --> 00:10:09.108
Mm-hm.

141
00:10:09.191 --> 00:10:10.526
What?

142
00:10:10.610 --> 00:10:12.695
-Are you gonna ask?
-Ask what?

143
00:10:12.778 --> 00:10:14.572
-About you-know-who.
-About Staten?

144
00:10:14.655 --> 00:10:15.656
-Yes.
-No.

145
00:10:15.740 --> 00:10:18.451
Well. he's been showing up here. Okay?

146
00:10:18.534 --> 00:10:20.995
-Asks after you.
-Hm.

147
00:10:21.621 --> 00:10:24.624
I mean. sure. he's had his.
you know. dalliances.

148
00:10:24.707 --> 00:10:25.958
but that's…

149
00:10:26.042 --> 00:10:28.502
Dalliances?
Is that what we're calling them?

150
00:10:28.586 --> 00:10:30.463
Okay. to be fair. so have you.

151
00:10:31.547 --> 00:10:34.634
Yeah. well.
a lot can happen in six months.

152
00:10:34.717 --> 00:10:36.552
You're telling me.

153
00:10:38.137 --> 00:10:41.974
Speaking of. what's the latest
and greatest with Yancy Gray

154
00:10:42.058 --> 00:10:44.644
and the whole long-lost wife situation?

155
00:10:48.397 --> 00:10:52.068
♪ Heaven knows I've seen darkness ♪

156
00:10:53.903 --> 00:10:55.696
♪ And I've seen what it can do ♪

157
00:10:57.823 --> 00:11:01.369
♪ Wooooo ♪

158
00:11:02.286 --> 00:11:05.831
♪ There's a storm that's on its way ♪

159
00:11:08.209 --> 00:11:10.836
♪ Wooo oooh. wooo oooh ♪

160
00:11:12.922 --> 00:11:14.632
♪ Wooo oooh. wooo oooh ♪

161
00:11:14.715 --> 00:11:15.758
Sidney?

162
00:11:19.929 --> 00:11:21.222
Where the hell are…

163
00:11:21.764 --> 00:11:23.599
Jesus Christ.

164
00:11:23.683 --> 00:11:26.519
-Can you put on clothes?
-Nothing you haven't seen before.

165
00:11:27.561 --> 00:11:30.898
Where are my beers?
And my barbecue? That was my lunch.

166
00:11:30.981 --> 00:11:33.901
-I'm trying to keep my hubby healthy.
-Don't call me that.

167
00:11:33.984 --> 00:11:36.779
Well. if the shoe fits. babe. Ooh.

168
00:11:36.862 --> 00:11:38.823
Speaking of shoes…

169
00:11:39.490 --> 00:11:42.702
I think these will go great with that
little dress I have with cherries on it.

170
00:11:42.785 --> 00:11:46.580
I wore it when we fleeced
that surly contractor back in Dallas.

171
00:11:46.664 --> 00:11:49.500
Come on. What is this? I…

172
00:11:50.668 --> 00:11:53.713
I have been patient. I've been kind.

173
00:11:53.796 --> 00:11:56.215
I've been sleeping
in the guest room for six months.

174
00:11:56.298 --> 00:11:58.467
You're always welcome in my bed.

175
00:12:00.511 --> 00:12:04.557
You said you needed help. place to lay low
after a job gone bad. I gave it to you.

176
00:12:04.640 --> 00:12:07.768
And you promised me
that you'd give me a divorce if I did.

177
00:12:07.852 --> 00:12:08.978
We had a deal.

178
00:12:09.061 --> 00:12:10.062
Okay. fine.

179
00:12:12.148 --> 00:12:14.400
I'll leave. If that's what you want.

180
00:12:15.192 --> 00:12:16.569
Okay.

181
00:12:16.652 --> 00:12:18.738
And… Thank you.

182
00:12:18.821 --> 00:12:20.656
Okay. I mean it. I just…

183
00:12:21.157 --> 00:12:24.201
I think it's best for both of us.
we go our separate ways.

184
00:12:24.285 --> 00:12:26.829
You mean so you can get back
with your hot bartender ex?

185
00:12:26.912 --> 00:12:29.206
I think I deserve the truth. is that it?

186
00:12:29.290 --> 00:12:31.542
No. That's over.

187
00:12:31.625 --> 00:12:34.378
It was over the minute
you arrived here in town.

188
00:12:34.462 --> 00:12:36.046
Perfect timing. Thank you.

189
00:12:36.130 --> 00:12:39.175
-Well. it wasn't me that lied to her.
-I didn't lie.

190
00:12:39.258 --> 00:12:41.385
You and I both know
our marriage was part of a con.

191
00:12:41.469 --> 00:12:43.596
one that I trusted was annulled.

192
00:12:43.679 --> 00:12:45.347
I just need to know if you're...

193
00:12:45.431 --> 00:12:47.850
-I said I'm gonna leave. all right?
-Then do it.

194
00:12:49.101 --> 00:12:50.102
Please.

195
00:13:14.668 --> 00:13:15.878
Staten?

196
00:13:20.132 --> 00:13:21.217
Hi there.

197
00:13:21.300 --> 00:13:24.094
Oh. Hey!

198
00:13:26.555 --> 00:13:27.765
It's good to see you.

199
00:13:27.848 --> 00:13:30.434
I could tell by how fast
you were trying to get out.

200
00:13:30.518 --> 00:13:34.980
Oh. yeah. I forgot I had to…
I had this thing I had to go… Yeah.

201
00:13:37.691 --> 00:13:39.944
I was sorry to hear about Double K.

202
00:13:40.027 --> 00:13:41.862
Your dad contesting you as trustee.

203
00:13:41.946 --> 00:13:44.114
No. I… Are you really that surprised?

204
00:13:45.783 --> 00:13:48.619
Well. hey. it ain't over
till it's over. right?

205
00:13:50.412 --> 00:13:51.455
Right.

206
00:13:53.999 --> 00:13:55.167
Good to see you.

207
00:13:55.251 --> 00:13:56.377
You said that.

208
00:13:56.460 --> 00:13:59.713
I feel like
we owe ourselves a conversation.

209
00:13:59.797 --> 00:14:01.715
-Is that right?
-Yeah.

210
00:14:01.799 --> 00:14:02.800
Huh.

211
00:14:02.883 --> 00:14:05.344
I don't recall my phone ringing
once these last six months.

212
00:14:05.427 --> 00:14:08.389
-Oh.
-Guess I just figured you'd moved on.

213
00:14:08.973 --> 00:14:11.934
In fact. I heard you had. What was it? Uh…

214
00:14:13.686 --> 00:14:17.022
Ransom's newest bicycle.
Everyone gets a ride.

215
00:14:18.732 --> 00:14:21.151
-That's funny.
-No judgment. You're a grown man.

216
00:14:21.235 --> 00:14:23.529
The phone rings both ways. doesn't it?

217
00:14:23.612 --> 00:14:25.072
True. Yeah.

218
00:14:25.155 --> 00:14:27.074
I don't remember getting a call from you.

219
00:14:27.157 --> 00:14:30.744
Yeah. But only one person
walked out the door that night.

220
00:14:30.828 --> 00:14:32.872
What did you want me to do? Call? Text?

221
00:14:32.955 --> 00:14:35.416
Send flowers? Fly to New York.
beg you to come back?

222
00:14:35.499 --> 00:14:36.500
No.

223
00:14:36.584 --> 00:14:37.960
No. I'm good.

224
00:14:38.043 --> 00:14:39.211
I've moved past it.

225
00:14:39.295 --> 00:14:40.421
Have you now?

226
00:14:42.381 --> 00:14:46.427
I think the universe has been trying to
tell us something for a long time. Staten.

227
00:14:46.927 --> 00:14:49.555
I think it's high time
we finally listened.

228
00:15:09.491 --> 00:15:11.118
Hey there. cowboy.

229
00:15:27.551 --> 00:15:29.136
She's gotta go.

230
00:15:29.219 --> 00:15:33.557
It's hard to believe anything
that comes out of that woman's mouth.

231
00:15:33.641 --> 00:15:37.311
I said it since the day she set foot
in Ransom. She wants you back.

232
00:15:38.145 --> 00:15:41.065
She's shit out of luck.
'cause I'm good and well taken.

233
00:15:41.148 --> 00:15:42.274
Damn right.

234
00:15:43.067 --> 00:15:44.234
You are.

235
00:15:51.533 --> 00:15:53.327
Maybe we should just tell her.

236
00:15:54.328 --> 00:15:57.206
Force her hand. you know? Make her leave.

237
00:15:57.957 --> 00:16:01.835
No. No. El… I've told you.

238
00:16:01.919 --> 00:16:03.504
Sid is a con artist.

239
00:16:03.587 --> 00:16:05.214
She's always working an angle.

240
00:16:05.297 --> 00:16:08.175
If she gets anything.
any crumb of information.

241
00:16:08.258 --> 00:16:09.760
she will use it against us.

242
00:16:09.843 --> 00:16:11.971
We cannot have that.

243
00:16:13.305 --> 00:16:14.306
Not now.

244
00:16:16.350 --> 00:16:19.645
My patience… is running thin.

245
00:16:20.896 --> 00:16:24.024
I went from about to get married
to secret girlfriend in one night.

246
00:16:24.108 --> 00:16:25.109
I know.

247
00:16:25.734 --> 00:16:26.734
I'm sorry.

248
00:16:27.194 --> 00:16:29.989
But look. if we play this right.

249
00:16:30.781 --> 00:16:32.449
we're gonna be in the clear.

250
00:16:34.785 --> 00:16:38.789
I'll swing by Gracie's tonight.
It'll just be you and me. Okay?

251
00:16:40.499 --> 00:16:41.500
Okay.

252
00:16:54.763 --> 00:16:56.098
The hell's all this?

253
00:16:57.474 --> 00:16:59.601
It's a… it's a catio.

254
00:17:00.102 --> 00:17:02.354
Okay? For Mr. Scratch.

255
00:17:03.647 --> 00:17:05.024
That stray cat?

256
00:17:06.025 --> 00:17:08.694
We don't even know
if that fleabag is a mister. Kit.

257
00:17:08.777 --> 00:17:10.904
You can't feed the thing
without getting cut up.

258
00:17:10.988 --> 00:17:14.783
-Why do you think it needs a catio?
-Look. there's no work. Okay?

259
00:17:14.867 --> 00:17:18.328
I've been losing my mind
since the Collins shuttered Bar W.

260
00:17:18.829 --> 00:17:23.292
Makes me sick watching you working every
weekend. You should be saving for college.

261
00:17:23.375 --> 00:17:25.461
-I'm happy to help.
-You wanna help?

262
00:17:26.712 --> 00:17:30.257
Put in a good word for me at the Double K.
Ranching's what I'm good at.

263
00:17:30.340 --> 00:17:32.176
Staten will be at the party tonight.

264
00:17:32.259 --> 00:17:34.845
-Come on. You know I can't do that.
-Can't?

265
00:17:35.846 --> 00:17:36.722
Or won't?

266
00:17:38.265 --> 00:17:40.768
Won't. Think Staten's gonna hire the guy

267
00:17:40.851 --> 00:17:43.687
who helped cover up the accident
that killed his kid?

268
00:17:44.271 --> 00:17:47.524
Shit. he'd fire me for even asking.
and I wouldn't blame him.

269
00:17:58.577 --> 00:18:00.662
You don't get it. It's really bad.

270
00:18:00.746 --> 00:18:02.498
Maybe it's not as bad as you think.

271
00:18:02.581 --> 00:18:05.125
My sister thought she bombed the SATs.
and now she's at Duke.

272
00:18:05.209 --> 00:18:09.129
-I didn't even finish. so…
-Sure you can't come back to the team?

273
00:18:09.213 --> 00:18:11.924
I can't even lift my arm.
so I'm gonna say no.

274
00:18:13.592 --> 00:18:16.678
Besides. you're doing great
as team captain.

275
00:18:16.762 --> 00:18:18.764
Doesn't mean you aren't missed.

276
00:18:20.682 --> 00:18:21.682
Hey.

277
00:18:23.060 --> 00:18:24.103
Come here.

278
00:18:25.771 --> 00:18:26.855
It's okay.

279
00:18:27.648 --> 00:18:29.066
It's gonna be okay.

280
00:18:38.408 --> 00:18:39.408
You good. boss?

281
00:18:40.327 --> 00:18:41.328
Yeah.

282
00:18:42.996 --> 00:18:47.751
I'm just weighing the state of things.
What are you all gussied up for?

283
00:18:47.835 --> 00:18:51.130
Thanks for noticing.
Quinn's welcome home party.

284
00:18:53.841 --> 00:18:55.008
Yeah.

285
00:18:55.092 --> 00:18:56.135
So…

286
00:18:57.678 --> 00:18:59.346
The old man's been on fire.

287
00:18:59.429 --> 00:19:04.351
Told the boys to plow up the Johnson
grass. replace it all with Sudan tomorrow.

288
00:19:04.434 --> 00:19:06.311
You wanna push back?

289
00:19:07.104 --> 00:19:08.272
No. Hell no.

290
00:19:09.648 --> 00:19:11.400
I'm gonna stick to the plan.

291
00:19:11.900 --> 00:19:13.819
I'm gonna let him hang himself.

292
00:19:14.653 --> 00:19:18.198
That way. in a couple of months.
when that trustee vote comes back around.

293
00:19:19.283 --> 00:19:22.244
the boys will know exactly
who to throw their vote behind.

294
00:19:25.998 --> 00:19:28.375
If he burns the Double K down
in the meantime?

295
00:19:29.126 --> 00:19:30.169
Well…

296
00:19:31.545 --> 00:19:34.631
Sometimes you gotta burn it down
to build it back up.

297
00:19:35.591 --> 00:19:37.467
Come back stronger. now.

298
00:19:38.760 --> 00:19:39.928
Mm.

299
00:19:42.139 --> 00:19:44.099
See you over at Gracie's tonight.

300
00:19:44.766 --> 00:19:46.268
I never said I was coming.

301
00:19:47.644 --> 00:19:49.897
Hell. We both know you're coming.

302
00:20:20.719 --> 00:20:21.929
What's up. Quinn?

303
00:20:23.847 --> 00:20:25.057
All right. let's go.

304
00:20:46.787 --> 00:20:47.829
Hey. you.

305
00:20:49.039 --> 00:20:51.124
Oh. sorry. I thought you were…

306
00:20:53.877 --> 00:20:55.045
Wait. who is this?

307
00:20:56.880 --> 00:20:58.924
-When you get back.
-I knew it.

308
00:21:00.717 --> 00:21:03.595
I knew you weren't just here
to see us. You're full of shit.

309
00:21:03.679 --> 00:21:06.139
-Quinn. honey.
-What's going on?

310
00:21:06.223 --> 00:21:09.643
I just got off the phone with a realtor.
Mom's trying to sell the house.

311
00:21:09.726 --> 00:21:13.063
"You know what you should do. honey?
Go back to New York."

312
00:21:13.146 --> 00:21:15.524
You… You should go back
to New York. I meant that.

313
00:21:15.607 --> 00:21:17.109
Are you trying to sell the house?

314
00:21:17.192 --> 00:21:19.194
I wasn't trying to go behind y'all's back.

315
00:21:19.278 --> 00:21:22.030
I wanted to have this conversation
after your party.

316
00:21:22.114 --> 00:21:26.201
Oh. that's so nice.
Thank you. Thank you for thinking of me.

317
00:21:26.285 --> 00:21:28.453
Excuse me. I was thinking of you.

318
00:21:28.537 --> 00:21:30.038
Of evicting me?

319
00:21:30.122 --> 00:21:34.251
Because the realtor said there is
a handful of very interested buyers.

320
00:21:34.334 --> 00:21:35.460
Jesus. Mom!

321
00:21:35.544 --> 00:21:37.129
This town is dying.

322
00:21:37.212 --> 00:21:40.674
The value of the farm is dipping
by the minute. Time to sell was yesterday.

323
00:21:40.757 --> 00:21:42.801
Even if that is true. you can't...

324
00:21:42.884 --> 00:21:45.554
I can. Because I own the property.

325
00:21:45.637 --> 00:21:47.806
And I make decisions regarding it.

326
00:21:49.516 --> 00:21:50.516
Perfect.

327
00:21:50.559 --> 00:21:53.020
Mom. I have to go to my party.

328
00:21:54.313 --> 00:21:57.482
And I have to act surprised.
Thank you very much.

329
00:21:58.317 --> 00:21:59.443
Can we still come?

330
00:22:01.194 --> 00:22:02.654
Do whatever you want.

331
00:22:03.655 --> 00:22:05.615
It's what you always do anyway.

332
00:22:09.494 --> 00:22:11.163
Claire. Claire…

333
00:22:12.831 --> 00:22:14.708
That's gonna take a while to mend.

334
00:22:15.334 --> 00:22:16.918
Maybe just tonight.

335
00:22:24.885 --> 00:22:26.303
♪ That ass from Alabama ♪

336
00:22:26.386 --> 00:22:29.931
♪ And she wanna go shopping
And get crab legs in Atlanta ♪

337
00:22:30.015 --> 00:22:31.975
♪ And nobody say Miami ♪

338
00:22:32.059 --> 00:22:33.685
♪ But I say that don't matter ♪

339
00:22:33.769 --> 00:22:35.604
♪ Cuz she dress like a city girl ♪

340
00:22:35.687 --> 00:22:38.607
♪ That cook just like my grandma
And she ain't from Tennessee ♪

341
00:22:38.690 --> 00:22:40.776
♪ But she a ten in my eyes ♪

342
00:22:40.859 --> 00:22:44.404
♪ And she mine Lord. willing
And the river gon' rise ♪

343
00:22:44.488 --> 00:22:45.947
♪ Cutie in a Louie ♪

344
00:22:46.031 --> 00:22:48.825
♪ Look like her mama raised her well ♪

345
00:22:48.909 --> 00:22:50.827
♪ Yeah ♪

346
00:22:50.911 --> 00:22:52.954
♪ Yeah. she know what she doin' ♪

347
00:22:53.038 --> 00:22:54.998
♪ So whatever she doin' ♪

348
00:22:55.082 --> 00:22:58.126
♪ Know that she gon' do it to death. hey ♪

349
00:22:58.210 --> 00:23:01.630
♪ Call her Monday she at work
She at work ♪

350
00:23:01.713 --> 00:23:05.217
♪ Call her Sunday she might be at church
Be at church ♪

351
00:23:05.300 --> 00:23:08.637
♪ Baby daddy got the baby
For the weekend ♪

352
00:23:08.720 --> 00:23:12.349
♪ So On Friday she gon' twerk
She gon' twerk ♪

353
00:23:12.432 --> 00:23:15.602
♪ She a demon in a dress
She stay on that typa time ♪

354
00:23:15.685 --> 00:23:19.398
♪ And she mine. lord. willing
And the river gon' rise ♪

355
00:23:20.023 --> 00:23:21.942
What the hell are you doing here?

356
00:23:22.025 --> 00:23:25.070
I'm showing off my new dress.
It's a party. isn't it?

357
00:23:25.153 --> 00:23:28.198
God. don't you just love it here?
You and me.

358
00:23:28.281 --> 00:23:30.617
Ransom elevens in a sea of fives.

359
00:23:33.036 --> 00:23:34.913
How about a dance? Hm?

360
00:23:35.497 --> 00:23:37.582
Come on. Come on.

361
00:23:43.630 --> 00:23:45.966
-Whiskey neat. Cheers.
-Thank you. Ellie.

362
00:23:49.928 --> 00:23:52.389
-I'll take one more.
-Make that two more.

363
00:23:56.017 --> 00:23:58.353
-I thought you might turn up.
-Yeah.

364
00:23:58.437 --> 00:23:59.813
Whole town turned up.

365
00:23:59.896 --> 00:24:03.483
Sure. But the whole town didn't
drench themselves in cologne.

366
00:24:03.567 --> 00:24:04.567
It's aftershave.

367
00:24:06.403 --> 00:24:08.363
It's a rare occasion I see you nervous.

368
00:24:08.447 --> 00:24:10.365
-I'm gonna enjoy it.
-I'm not nervous.

369
00:24:10.449 --> 00:24:13.368
Just like you're not buying me
this whiskey here.

370
00:24:13.452 --> 00:24:15.662
-Put both on his tab?
-You got it. Sheriff.

371
00:24:15.745 --> 00:24:16.997
Thank you. Ellie.

372
00:24:17.581 --> 00:24:20.375
Hey. thank you
for your service. Cheap ass.

373
00:24:20.876 --> 00:24:22.502
Don't you clean up nice?

374
00:24:23.295 --> 00:24:25.172
Aging well. too.

375
00:24:25.255 --> 00:24:28.467
Oh my God. Claire O'Grady.
what the hell are you doing here?

376
00:24:28.550 --> 00:24:30.760
-How's your Aunt Bea?
-She's dead.

377
00:24:30.844 --> 00:24:32.053
My condolences.

378
00:24:32.137 --> 00:24:34.514
-Two decades ago.
-Damn.

379
00:24:37.601 --> 00:24:40.770
I haven't seen you around here in ages.
What's the occasion?

380
00:24:40.854 --> 00:24:42.481
Oh. I'm back for Quinn's party.

381
00:24:42.564 --> 00:24:44.191
-Uh-huh.
-And the odd loose end or two.

382
00:24:44.274 --> 00:24:46.735
-Oh. loose ends. right.
-Mm-hm.

383
00:24:47.527 --> 00:24:48.528
How's the ranch?

384
00:24:48.612 --> 00:24:50.238
-It's awful.
-Mm.

385
00:24:50.947 --> 00:24:53.825
Still the charmer. Staten.

386
00:24:53.909 --> 00:24:56.745
-Whoo!
-Ever the angel. Claire.

387
00:24:56.828 --> 00:24:57.954
So nice to see you.

388
00:25:00.373 --> 00:25:01.541
Quinn?

389
00:25:04.294 --> 00:25:07.923
-Senator. Or should I say former?
-Mm.

390
00:25:08.006 --> 00:25:10.175
Shame about those election results.

391
00:25:10.258 --> 00:25:12.385
Depends on how you slice it.

392
00:25:14.888 --> 00:25:16.181
Nice seeing you. sir.

393
00:25:17.349 --> 00:25:18.517
Clear as day.

394
00:25:19.309 --> 00:25:23.313
You took down your own son and this town
for your own personal interests.

395
00:25:23.396 --> 00:25:26.816
I hope on your last days
you look back on that flawed decision

396
00:25:26.900 --> 00:25:28.693
with the regret that it deserves.

397
00:25:28.777 --> 00:25:29.861
Well…

398
00:25:31.571 --> 00:25:32.864
It's good to see you.

399
00:25:34.199 --> 00:25:35.408
You too. Sam.

400
00:25:40.247 --> 00:25:41.373
I love your work.

401
00:25:45.877 --> 00:25:46.878
Hi.

402
00:25:47.837 --> 00:25:49.130
Okay. be right back.

403
00:25:49.214 --> 00:25:52.300
That's what I said.

404
00:25:56.346 --> 00:25:57.556
We should all… yeah.

405
00:25:57.639 --> 00:25:59.599
-Hey. y'all.
-Hey!

406
00:25:59.683 --> 00:26:03.353
-I was telling Lucas. party at my place.
-You should both come.

407
00:26:04.437 --> 00:26:08.024
Yeah. I mean. like…
maybe. I just gotta clean.

408
00:26:08.108 --> 00:26:10.110
-So…
-We'll be going all night.

409
00:26:11.945 --> 00:26:13.363
We'll catch the next one.

410
00:26:14.281 --> 00:26:15.323
-Yeah.
-All right.

411
00:26:15.407 --> 00:26:16.741
Yeah. all good.

412
00:26:16.825 --> 00:26:19.286
Sorry. Uh… I'm gonna… I'm gonna go.

413
00:26:19.369 --> 00:26:20.579
Go. Go.

414
00:26:24.541 --> 00:26:26.001
You shouldn't do that.

415
00:26:26.751 --> 00:26:27.919
It's not a big deal.

416
00:26:28.503 --> 00:26:31.756
I'm just saying. don't dim your light.
'cause hers is flickering.

417
00:26:31.840 --> 00:26:33.341
What does that mean?

418
00:26:35.552 --> 00:26:37.012
Tell me what you mean.

419
00:26:38.513 --> 00:26:40.932
You wanna hit it real nice and soft.

420
00:26:41.516 --> 00:26:42.809
Just

421
00:26:43.977 --> 00:26:45.020
kiss it.

422
00:26:47.063 --> 00:26:48.565
Ah. scratch.

423
00:26:50.150 --> 00:26:51.401
Bummer.

424
00:26:51.484 --> 00:26:53.320
-Yeah.
-Hey. did you drop this?

425
00:26:54.154 --> 00:26:55.155
Yeah.

426
00:26:56.031 --> 00:26:57.324
-Thanks.
-No problem.

427
00:26:58.658 --> 00:27:02.579
What the hell was that?
When did you become so boring?

428
00:27:02.662 --> 00:27:04.247
-Jesus.
-I live here. Sid.

429
00:27:04.331 --> 00:27:07.000
I am aware of that.

430
00:27:07.500 --> 00:27:11.504
I left that life behind. I'm not gonna
have you screwing this up for me.

431
00:27:12.005 --> 00:27:15.759
You said that you're gonna go. gonna
give me a divorce. Gonna stand by that?

432
00:27:16.760 --> 00:27:17.886
I'm thinking on it.

433
00:27:19.179 --> 00:27:22.265
You're thinking on it?
Yeah. Yeah. that tracks.

434
00:27:22.932 --> 00:27:25.894
I know that you're playing
at something. Sid.

435
00:27:26.770 --> 00:27:28.688
So what is it? What do you want?

436
00:27:29.230 --> 00:27:30.440
I want you.

437
00:27:30.523 --> 00:27:34.778
I miss us. I mean. you and me against
the world. playing cons every single day.

438
00:27:34.861 --> 00:27:36.279
How great that felt.

439
00:27:36.863 --> 00:27:38.281
Don't you want that again?

440
00:27:39.949 --> 00:27:41.159
No.

441
00:27:41.242 --> 00:27:42.327
You do.

442
00:27:42.827 --> 00:27:44.412
You… you do.

443
00:27:45.747 --> 00:27:48.500
You're so good at grifting
that you are grifting yourself.

444
00:27:50.126 --> 00:27:54.547
You wanna spend the rest of your life
shoveling cow shit on a dying ranch?

445
00:27:56.174 --> 00:28:00.053
Tell me that is what you really want. and
I will sign the divorce papers tonight.

446
00:28:02.806 --> 00:28:03.973
That's what I want.

447
00:28:06.142 --> 00:28:09.854
If that's how you really feel.
I'll just. uh… I'll be on my way.

448
00:28:09.938 --> 00:28:11.898
Sid. I'm sorry.

449
00:28:15.860 --> 00:28:16.903
-Hey. Lauren.
-Hi.

450
00:28:16.986 --> 00:28:18.780
-Can we talk?
-I'm a busy. but...

451
00:28:18.863 --> 00:28:21.908
-Why are you lying to me?
-I can assure you I'm busy.

452
00:28:21.991 --> 00:28:22.992
About the SAT.

453
00:28:25.036 --> 00:28:29.666
Hey. don't. don't blame Ashley for telling
me. She's. uh… she's worried about you.

454
00:28:29.749 --> 00:28:31.251
Yeah. who's lying now?

455
00:28:31.334 --> 00:28:34.713
I don't care. I feel bad. Maybe I was
putting too much pressure on you.

456
00:28:34.796 --> 00:28:35.839
No. no. it's...

457
00:28:35.922 --> 00:28:38.049
-I need to know you trust me.
-Just stop.

458
00:28:38.133 --> 00:28:41.344
You… It's not your fault.
It's never your fault.

459
00:28:41.928 --> 00:28:46.349
I didn't say anything to you because
I didn't want to disappoint you. but I…

460
00:28:47.934 --> 00:28:50.061
I don't know if I'm going anywhere soon.

461
00:28:50.145 --> 00:28:52.605
And I'm not going anywhere without you.

462
00:28:52.689 --> 00:28:54.983
I'm not leaving you behind.
Not now. not ever.

463
00:28:55.066 --> 00:28:57.944
You say nice things. At the end
of the day. they're just words.

464
00:28:58.027 --> 00:29:01.489
They're not just words. Lauren.
My life is with you.

465
00:29:02.073 --> 00:29:03.199
And if that's here.

466
00:29:03.700 --> 00:29:04.951
maybe that is here.

467
00:29:06.077 --> 00:29:07.120
Okay?

468
00:29:08.496 --> 00:29:09.330
'Kay.

469
00:29:15.378 --> 00:29:16.588
Thank you.

470
00:29:18.840 --> 00:29:19.924
Yeah.

471
00:29:20.425 --> 00:29:22.385
Thanks for a hundred right there.

472
00:29:27.766 --> 00:29:29.684
Buy you fellas your next round?

473
00:29:30.185 --> 00:29:31.352
Huh?

474
00:29:31.436 --> 00:29:32.436
I'll pass.

475
00:29:33.396 --> 00:29:36.357
Any of y'all want to take
Mr. Kirkland up on his kindness?

476
00:29:36.441 --> 00:29:37.567
I'm good.

477
00:29:39.360 --> 00:29:40.360
I ain't thirsty.

478
00:29:49.120 --> 00:29:50.205
Mr. Kirkland.

479
00:29:52.957 --> 00:29:53.958
Kit Russell.

480
00:29:54.542 --> 00:29:56.878
I heard you're running things
at the Double K now.

481
00:29:56.961 --> 00:29:57.961
Mm-hm.

482
00:29:58.004 --> 00:30:02.926
By the looks of it. sir… could use a hand
to give you a bit of respect.

483
00:30:04.177 --> 00:30:05.595
That's a bold move.

484
00:30:05.678 --> 00:30:07.722
Especially coming from the shit-heel

485
00:30:07.806 --> 00:30:10.099
who tried to cover up
the death of my grandson.

486
00:30:11.851 --> 00:30:14.145
-Yeah. I did.
-Mm-hm.

487
00:30:14.771 --> 00:30:16.147
I was protecting someone.

488
00:30:17.023 --> 00:30:19.150
Kept my mouth shut out of loyalty.

489
00:30:19.234 --> 00:30:20.360
My hot take?

490
00:30:21.694 --> 00:30:23.279
You could use a bit of loyalty.

491
00:30:23.863 --> 00:30:26.991
You're never winning over
Staten's guys. Never.

492
00:30:29.869 --> 00:30:32.831
You'd be working cheek-to-cheek
with Staten every day.

493
00:30:32.914 --> 00:30:35.542
No. sir. I'd be working for you.

494
00:30:35.625 --> 00:30:37.502
Loyal as the day is long.

495
00:30:43.716 --> 00:30:44.801
Care for a drink?

496
00:30:44.884 --> 00:30:46.135
I'd be grateful.

497
00:30:47.178 --> 00:30:48.178
Boss.

498
00:31:04.863 --> 00:31:06.239
You were right about Sid.

499
00:31:06.322 --> 00:31:09.033
I knew it. She's back for you.

500
00:31:09.117 --> 00:31:11.369
Guess she was hanging on. hoping.

501
00:31:11.452 --> 00:31:12.704
Hm.

502
00:31:13.204 --> 00:31:15.164
But look. I made it damn clear.

503
00:31:15.248 --> 00:31:17.959
There is no future there.
I know that it landed.

504
00:31:18.042 --> 00:31:19.127
So it's over?

505
00:31:19.878 --> 00:31:20.920
She's leaving?

506
